      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ack. I\u0027d document why this is sure to be a file in the VirtualEnv\u0027s \"lib\" directory, which because it\u0027s in VirtualEnv\u0027s \"REQUIRED_MODULES\" list, which is always copied: https://github.com/pypa/virtualenv/blob/master/virtualenv.py#L120\n\nHowever, VirtualEnv is guaranteed to always drop a \"site.py\", so using that as the lookup base like you were before is probably better. In that case, I\u0027d document that VirtualEnv generates a \"site.py\" and that\u0027s what we\u0027re importing.\n\nAs an aside, looking at VirtualEnv\u0027s \"site.py\" template: https://github.com/pypa/virtualenv/blob/e9165093529371f7d3eaedf26e7bbcdc18445380/virtualenv_embedded/site.py#L678\n\nI see \"no-global-site-packages.txt\". This precludes the inclusion of a user\u0027s \"site.py\", which seems very much like something that we want to do. Maybe consider dropping this file into the VirtualEnv alongside \"site.py\" and \"sitecustomize.py\" is a good thing to do, too! You can use filesystem.Touch for that.",
      "parentUuid": "5b4a454c_bae57b8d",
